						<h4>Polly Barton</h4>
												<p>Polly Barton is a literary translator and writer. Her translations from Japanese to English include <em>Butter</em> by Asako Yuzuki, <em>The Woman Dies</em> and <em>Where the Wild Ladies Are</em> by Aoko Matsuda, and <em>There’s No Such Thing as an Easy Job</em> by Kikuko Tsumura. Her English-language translation of <em>Hunchback</em> by Saou Ichikawa was longlisted for the International Booker Prize 2025. Barton has written the books <em>Fifty Sounds and Porn: An Oral History</em>, both published by Fitzcarraldo Editions, and her debut novel <em>What am I, a Deer?</em> comes out in 2026.</p>
